    {
      "id": "b243",
      "type": "text",
      "data": {
        "text": "**2.** Follow with the six. You know partner is out of diamonds, but you can't be certain of the best line of defense, which depends on the layout. Accordingly, you should signal neutrally, suggesting roughly equal holdings in the candidate suits. If you play the deuce, partner will hope for you to have something like king-queen-fourth of clubs and may shift to a club, surrendering the contract. If you play the diamond six, partner will have a chance to find the necessary heart shift."
      }
    },
