    {
      "id": "b246",
      "type": "text",
      "data": {
        "text": "**3.** Win, cash the club king, and shift to a heart, preferably the king (to help partner). Don't underlead in clubs, because declarer has made a \"newspaper play,\" winning with the ace from ace-queen. With queen-jack of clubs, partner would have signaled his enthusiasm for that suit with an encouraging Smith signal.\n\nI view Smith as a necessity. BWS uses low in the suit declarer plays to encourage the opening-lead suit. When Smith first appeared, high was encouraging, so partners should ensure that they are on the same page."
      }
